  <!-- BODY -->
  <div class="post-body-wrap">
    <div class="post-grid">
      <article class="post-content">
        <p class="lede-p"><strong>Scalenut is the most workflow-complete AI content suite on the market.</strong> Cruise Mode genuinely generates a publishable-after-editing first draft in five minutes. It is also a tool that creates a different bottleneck: the editing queue. After 30 days inside Essential, Growth, and Pro — plus interviews with 11 paying customers — here is the honest 2026 verdict, where Scalenut beats Surfer + Jasper, and where it still leaves operators stuck.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Editorial disclosure</div>
          <p>This review was written and published by theStacc, a done-for-you SEO content service. We compete with Scalenut for the operator who is choosing between "buy AI tools and run the workflow" versus "outsource the workflow entirely". Every feature claim and price was verified against Scalenut's public pricing page as of Q2 2026.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="callout callout-tldr">
          <div class="callout-label">⚡ TL;DR — The 30-second verdict</div>
          <p><strong>Buy Scalenut if</strong> you have someone willing to edit AI drafts and ship them — Cruise Mode is the fastest "blank page to first draft" workflow we have tested. Essential at $59/mo is the easiest entry point. <strong>Skip it if</strong> you do not have editorial capacity — AI drafts pile up unread and the tool sits idle. If you want traffic without managing the editorial queue, theStacc handles writing, optimisation, and publishing end-to-end from $99/mo.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Want traffic, not an AI draft backlog?</h4>
            <p>Get a <strong>free SEO audit</strong> in 24 hours. We'll show you the keywords you're missing, the technical fixes that move the needle, and your competitors' content gaps — no sales call, no obligation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">Get my free audit <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">24-hour delivery · No card</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="vs-stacc">theStacc vs Scalenut — where we are honestly better (and worse)</h2>
        <p>We compete for the same buyer at a similar price point. Read the comparison first.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Scalenut</th><th>theStacc</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Starting price</td><td>$59/mo</td><td>$99/mo</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Cruise Mode (5-min AI drafts)</td><td class="cell-yes">Yes — fastest in category</td><td class="cell-no">Not the workflow</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Keyword + SERP research</td><td class="cell-yes">Built-in</td><td class="cell-yes">Built into briefs</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Content optimisation scoring</td><td class="cell-yes">In-editor</td><td>Applied to every article</td></tr>
              <tr><td>AI writing assist</td><td class="cell-yes">Strong</td><td class="cell-yes">Human-edited drafts</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Editorial review by humans</td><td class="cell-no">You edit</td><td class="cell-yes">Done for you</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Articles published to your CMS</td><td>WordPress (manual push)</td><td class="cell-yes">WordPress · Webflow · Ghost (auto)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Google Business Profile posts</td><td class="cell-no">No</td><td class="cell-yes">GBP posts included</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Done-for-you (no workflow to run)</td><td class="cell-no">DIY — you edit + ship</td><td class="cell-yes">Fully managed</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Real monthly cost for SEO content</strong></td><td>$1,200–$3,500 (tool + editor)</td><td><strong>$99 flat</strong></td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p><strong>Where Scalenut wins:</strong> if you have editorial capacity, Cruise Mode produces drafts faster than any other tool we tested. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if you do not want to manage the editorial queue or hit publish manually. Pick by the job, not the brand.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Scalenut?</h2>
        <p>Scalenut is an SEO content suite. It launched in 2021 and has grown into one of the most-talked-about AI content platforms in marketing circles. The product bundles features that traditionally required three separate tools: keyword/SERP research (like Ahrefs lite), an AI writer (like Jasper), and content optimisation scoring (like Surfer). The headline feature is <strong>Cruise Mode</strong> — a guided 5-step workflow that takes you from target keyword to publishable first draft in roughly five minutes.</p>

        <p>The product does six things:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Keyword planner</strong> — keyword discovery with volume and difficulty</li>
          <li><strong>SERP analyser</strong> — top-ranking pages with NLP-extracted terms</li>
          <li><strong>Content briefs</strong> — outlines, semantic terms, suggested word count</li>
          <li><strong>Cruise Mode</strong> — 5-minute AI-generated first draft</li>
          <li><strong>Content optimisation editor</strong> — real-time scoring against SERP</li>
          <li><strong>Internal link automation</strong> — suggests internal links across published content</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Scalenut is <em>not</em>: a fully autonomous publisher (you still review and ship), a backlink analyser, a rank tracker, or a local SEO suite. It compresses three tools into one — which is its biggest strength and the source of most criticism (it does many things, none perfectly).</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>Scalenut was founded in 2021 by Mayank Jain and Saurabh Wadhawan. The company is based in India and has raised meaningful seed/Series A funding. The team has shipped aggressively — Cruise Mode was a top-of-Product-Hunt launch and has driven the product's recent growth. Customer base is concentrated in SMB marketing teams and digital agencies, with a strong presence in the US and EMEA.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">Scalenut features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is broad for the price. Here is what matters in daily use.</p>

        <h3>1. Cruise Mode — the flagship</h3>
        <p>Drop in a target keyword. Scalenut walks you through five guided steps in roughly five minutes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Step 1: Context</strong> — choose your audience, tone, and the article's goal</li>
          <li><strong>Step 2: Title</strong> — pick from AI-generated titles or write your own</li>
          <li><strong>Step 3: Outline</strong> — review and edit AI-suggested H2s/H3s pulled from the SERP</li>
          <li><strong>Step 4: Generation</strong> — AI writes section copy for each subheading</li>
          <li><strong>Step 5: Optimisation</strong> — review final draft against the SERP score</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Output quality is genuinely better than blank-page ChatGPT because the model is grounded in SERP data. Still needs human editing for fact accuracy, original analysis, and the brand voice — but as a "from zero to 80% draft" tool, nothing else in this price tier matches it.</p>

        <h3>2. Keyword planner + SERP analyser</h3>
        <p>Scalenut's keyword data is solid for primary research but thinner than Ahrefs or Semrush. The SERP analyser is genuinely useful — it surfaces ranking pages, their semantic terms, word counts, schema usage, and structural patterns. Often eliminates the need to bounce into Ahrefs for the brief stage of work.</p>

        <h3>3. Content briefs</h3>
        <p>Briefs include H2/H3 suggestions, semantic terms grouped by importance, FAQ ideas pulled from People Also Ask, and a target word count. Shareable with writers via link. Quality is on par with Surfer's briefs, slightly less noisy than Frase.</p>

        <h3>4. Content optimisation editor</h3>
        <p>Real-time scoring as you write or paste. The scoring methodology is competitive with Surfer's. Side-panel shows missing terms, frequency targets, and a content score out of 100. Hit 80+ and you are competitive with ranking pages.</p>

        <h3>5. Internal link automation</h3>
        <p>This is a feature we have not seen done well elsewhere. Scalenut crawls your published content and automatically suggests internal links between articles based on semantic similarity. Saves hours of manual link-mapping for sites with 50+ articles.</p>

        <h3>6. WordPress integration</h3>
        <p>Push drafts directly to WordPress as drafts or scheduled posts. You still log into WordPress to review and publish — it is not fully automated like theStacc or Outrank's autopilot mode, but it removes the copy-paste step.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ The editorial bottleneck</div>
          <p>Cruise Mode generates drafts faster than most teams can edit them. In our testing the bottleneck moved from "writing" to "reviewing AI drafts". If you do not have editorial capacity behind the tool, you will accumulate drafts that never ship — and the tool will quietly sit unused.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="pricing">Scalenut pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>Scalenut publishes transparent pricing and offers a 7-day free trial across all paid plans.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Monthly</th><th>Annual / mo</th><th>Articles/mo</th><th>Seats</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Essential</strong></td><td>$59</td><td>~$39</td><td>5</td><td>1</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Growth</strong></td><td>$149</td><td>~$99</td><td>40</td><td>1</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Pro</strong></td><td>$199</td><td>~$159</td><td>70</td><td>3</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Enterprise</strong></td><td>Custom</td><td>Custom</td><td>Unlimited</td><td>Custom</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>For the entry tier, Essential at $59/mo is competitive with Frase ($45/mo) and significantly cheaper than Surfer Essential ($119/mo). Growth at $149/mo is the most popular plan based on customer interviews.</p>

        <h3>The real monthly cost most reviews skip</h3>
        <p>Scalenut's tool cost is cheap. The cost of an editor to handle the AI output and the time spent in WordPress publishing is not.</p>

        <!-- Interactive cost calculator -->
        <div class="cost-calc">
          <div class="cc-head">
            <div>
              <h4>The true monthly cost of SEO content with Scalenut</h4>
              <p>Tool is fast. Editing AI drafts and publishing is not.</p>
            </div>
