            <div class="cc-row cc-row-total"><span>What you actually spend</span><strong>$3,349 /mo</strong></div>
          </div>
          <div class="cc-vs">
            <span class="cc-vs-label">VS theStacc</span>
            <div class="cc-vs-row">
              <span>theStacc Bundle — content done for you, expert-reviewed, auto-published</span>
              <strong>$167 /mo</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="cc-save">
              <span>You save</span>
              <span><strong>$3,182 /mo</strong> · or <strong>$38,184 / year</strong></span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cc-foot">
            <p>Want the AI workflow without owning the editorial queue? Let's see if your site qualifies.</p>
            <a href="/demo/">Get my free audit →</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta dark">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Stop generating drafts. Start publishing articles.</h4>
            <p>We'll audit your site and show you exactly what would generate the highest ROI for <strong>your</strong> business — DIY tool, agency, or done-for-you platform.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">Book my strategy call <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">30-min · No pitch</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="pros-cons">Pros and cons after 30 days</h2>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros-card">
            <h4>✓ What Scalenut gets right</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Cruise Mode is the fastest blank-page-to-draft workflow tested</li>
              <li>Bundles 3 tools into one (research + AI + scoring)</li>
              <li>Essential at $59/mo is competitive entry pricing</li>
              <li>Internal link automation is genuinely unique</li>
              <li>Content scoring rivals Surfer's accuracy</li>
              <li>WordPress integration removes copy-paste step</li>
              <li>SERP analyser is solid replacement for Ahrefs-lite briefing</li>
              <li>7-day free trial across all paid plans</li>
              <li>Fast support and active product team</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons-card">
            <h4>✗ Where Scalenut hurts</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>AI output still needs heavy editing for fact accuracy</li>
              <li>Cruise Mode drafts are recognisably AI without editing</li>
              <li>Keyword data is thinner than Ahrefs or Semrush</li>
              <li>WordPress publishing is not fully automated</li>
              <li>No backlink analysis or rank tracking</li>
              <li>No local SEO or Google Business Profile</li>
              <li>UI density can overwhelm new users</li>
              <li>Bundles "good enough" features rather than best-in-class</li>
              <li>Editorial bottleneck moves to drafts piling up unedited</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Don't want to manage an editorial queue?</h4>
            <p>theStacc handles audits, content, publishing, GBP, and rank tracking — without you ever opening an AI editor. <strong>Try it for $1</strong>, cancel anytime.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/checkout/" class="cta-btn-inline">Start $1 trial <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No annual contract</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="performance">Performance benchmarks — how Scalenut stacks up</h2>
        <p>We generated 10 articles in Cruise Mode and compared output and time-to-publish against Surfer + Jasper and Frase Solo.</p>

        <div class="stat-grid">
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">~5</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Min to first draft</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">Cruise Mode</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">$59</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">/mo Essential</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">vs Surfer $119</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">40</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Articles/mo on Growth</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">Most teams ship 8–12</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">~45</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Min editing/article</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">to ship-quality</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Scalenut vs Surfer + Jasper vs Frase</h3>

        <div class="chart-card">
          <div class="chart-head">
            <div>
              <div class="chart-title">Tool comparison (out of 10)</div>
              <div class="chart-sub">10 articles · same keywords · scored May 2026</div>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-legend">
              <span class="lg-1">Scalenut</span>
              <span class="lg-2">Competitors</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-rows">
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Time to first draft</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="width: 94%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">9.4</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Workflow completeness</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="width: 90%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">9.0</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Surfer + Jasper combo</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill alt" style="width: 88%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">8.8</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Frase Solo</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill alt" style="width: 76%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">7.6</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Draft quality (before editing)</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="width: 76%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">7.6</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Auto-publishing</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="width: 40%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">4.0</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>Scalenut wins on speed and workflow completeness. Surfer + Jasper wins on best-in-class scoring and writing. Frase wins on price. None of them fully automate publishing — that gap is consistent across all AI content tools.</p>

        <blockquote class="pull">
          "We bought Scalenut because Cruise Mode is genuinely fast. Six months in, we realised our bottleneck was never writing — it was reviewing what the AI wrote. The drafts piled up. We never published a third of them."
