        <h2 id="verdict">Is Scalenut worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For teams with editorial capacity: yes — Cruise Mode is the fastest workflow we have tested.</strong> Essential at $59/mo is a strong entry; Growth at $149/mo is where most successful teams settle.</p>

        <p><strong>For agencies producing content at scale across clients: yes, especially the Pro plan.</strong> The workflow consolidation (research + AI + scoring + WordPress push) is genuinely valuable for content velocity.</p>

        <p><strong>For solo founders or anyone without an editor: almost always no.</strong> The bottleneck moves to editing. AI drafts pile up. The tool quietly stops earning its subscription. If you do not have someone who can spend 45 minutes per article on review, fact-checking, and polish, the math does not work.</p>

