            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Scalenut is an SEO content suite. It combines keyword planner, SERP analyser, content briefs, an AI-powered editor with Cruise Mode (5-minute first-draft generation), content optimisation scoring, and an internal-link automation layer. It is positioned as an all-in-one alternative to Surfer + Frase + Jasper.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How much does Scalenut cost in 2026?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Essential is $59/mo (5 articles, 100k AI words), Growth is $149/mo (40 articles, unlimited AI words), Pro is $199/mo (70 articles, team seats). Annual billing offers a discount. Higher tiers add more articles per month, more SEO reports, and more team seats.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is Cruise Mode in Scalenut?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Cruise Mode is Scalenut's flagship feature. It generates a full SEO-optimised first draft in roughly five minutes from a target keyword. It pulls SERP data, suggests an outline, generates section copy, and scores against ranking competitors. The output still needs human editing for accuracy and original perspective.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is Scalenut better than Surfer SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Scalenut bundles AI writing with optimisation in one tool; Surfer is optimisation-first with optional AI add-ons. For teams wanting one tool for brief + draft + scoring, Scalenut wins on workflow. For teams that already have writers and only need scoring, Surfer is cleaner. Pricing is comparable at the entry tier.</p></div></div>
